ProtoResult:
. "Let $m$ and $n$ be positive integers such that $\gcd( m, n)
= 1$. Then for $a, b \in {\mathbb Z}$ the system
\[
  \begin{aligned}
    x & \equiv a \pmod{m} \\
    x & \equiv b \pmod{n}
  \end{aligned}
\]
has a solution. If $x_1$ and $x_2$ are
two solutions of the system, then $x_1 \equiv x_2 \pmod{mn}$."
